# Trine environment variables
# Copy to `.env` for local dev (`netlify dev`) and set the same in Netlify UI.

# --- Client (exposed to the browser; safe — anon key is RLS-guarded) ---
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# --- Server (Netlify function only; NEVER prefixed with VITE_) ---
# Without this, the curate function returns an illustrative demo shortlist.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# --- Retailer feeds (optional). With these, /app returns REAL listings ---
# ranked by Claude instead of AI-generated picks with search links.
# eBay: either a static Browse token, OR client id/secret (auto-minted, preferred).
EBAY_CLIENT_ID=
EBAY_CLIENT_SECRET=
EBAY_ACCESS_TOKEN=
# Best Buy: a free Developer API key.
BESTBUY_API_KEY=

# --- Scraped retailers via Firecrawl (optional, paid per request) ---
# When set, /app also pulls Amazon, The RealReal, and Nordstrom — which have no
# usable free product API. Scraping (8-60s) runs in the scrape-warm-background
# function and fills the scraped_products cache; curate only READS the cache, so
# user requests stay fast. Get a key at https://www.firecrawl.dev.
FIRECRAWL_API_KEY=
# Service role key (Supabase Dashboard → Project Settings → API). Used ONLY by
# the background scraper to write the scraped_products cache (server-side secret,
# never sent to the browser). curate reads the cache with the anon key above.
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=
